    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="3"><b>NEW! Group Reporting feature now available for System Administrators.</b></font>
    <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="2">
    <br><br>
    Group Reporting now offers new management reports along with the ability to request reports on groups of users providing details on all users rather than one at a time.
    <br><br>
    Accessible via the activity tab, this timesaving feature offers:
    <br><br>
    <b>User Reporting</b>
    <ul>
	Activity Report -- Provides a report of search activity on a particular user for a given time period.
	<br>
	Summary Report -- This report contains a high level summary of a user's activity. You can only run one user at a time with this report.
    </ul>
    <b>Group Reporting</b>
    <ul>
	Detailed Report -- This report provides a detailed overview of a Group's activity.
	<br>
	Summary Report -- This report contains a high level summary of a Group's activity.
    </ul>
    <b>User List Reporting</b>
    <ul>
	This report provides the ability to pull all users, active only, or inactive only.
    </ul>
    <b>Management Reporting</b>
    <ul>
	Management Feature Report -- This report contains a detailed list of the status of Group features across all available billgroups.
	<br>
	Management Group Report -- This report provides a detailed report on users/groups within the selected billgroup(s).
    </ul>
    Learn more!&nbsp; <b><a href="https://learn.lexisnexis.com/lexisnexis/user_activity_info.aspx?id=822" target="_blank"><u>Click here</u></a> to download a complimentary System Administrator user guide.</b>
    <br><br>
